# Security Brain — paths and conventions

Canonical layout (`brain/00-meta/README.md`):

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `01-frameworks/` | CSF, SOC 2, ISO overviews and crosswalks |
| `02-controls/` | Control catalog (`cloud-checks.yaml`) |
| `03-policies/` | **Authoritative** policies |
| `03-policies/proposals/` | Draft policy redlines (A1) — promote here after review |
| `evidence/<CC-slug>/` | Evidence indexes (MVP active path) |
| `04-standards/` … `08-decisions/` | Standards, procedures, risks, decisions |

## Where to write what

| Content | Path | Notes |
|---------|------|-------|
| Policy redline (draft) | `brain/03-policies/proposals/<policy-slug>-redline.md` | kebab-case slug; mark **DRAFT** |
| Authoritative policy | `brain/03-policies/<policy-slug>.md` | A4 — human publish only |
| Evidence index | `brain/evidence/<CC-slug>/index-<YYYYMMDD>.md` | slug: dots → hyphens (`CC6.1` → `CC6-1`) |
| Cloud findings | `brain/evidence/<CC-slug>/findings-<YYYYMMDD>.json` | optional; from evidence-pack |
| Framework / control docs | `01-frameworks/`, `02-controls/` | human-reviewed brain content |

## Evidence-pack path (governed)

Prefer `spa` with repo root as output so files land in git-backed brain:

```bash
spa run-skill evidence-pack --input <file> --output-dir .
# → brain/evidence/CC6-1/index-20260607.md
```

Input must include `Control: CC6.1` and `Period: 2026-Q2` (or similar).

## Policy redline flow

1. Skill stages at `workspace/proposals/03-policies/proposals/<slug>-redline.md`
2. After human review → copy/promote to `brain/03-policies/proposals/<slug>-redline.md`
3. Publish to `brain/03-policies/<slug>.md` only with A4 approval

## After substantive edits

```bash
make seed   # re-index brain → Qdrant semantic memory
```

## Control IDs in brain

- SOC 2 CC notation: `CC6.1` in docs; directory slug `CC6-1` under `evidence/`
- Cloud checks in `02-controls/cloud-checks.yaml` use CC keys per provider (`aws`, `gcp`)
